Key Match Events: Immanuel Quickley scored 21 points and made 15 assists after missing the Raptors’ last 22 games.
Toronto Raptors beat the Brooklyn Nets 130-113 to snap an 11-game losing skid.
Scottie Barnes led all scorers with 33 points and 13 rebounds.
Post-Match Reflections: Immanuel Quickley expressed gratitude for being able to compete again after his injury.
Quickley emphasized the importance of building a culture of winning, enthusiasm, joy, and unselfishness.
Scottie Barnes highlighted RJ Barrett's potential impact on the team's performance upon his return.
